adjectives.description: inficete (comparative more inficete, superlative most inficete)

examples: MR. EAVESDROP: Sir, you are very facetious at my expense.THE REV. DR. FOLLIOTT: Sir, you have been very unfacetious, very inficete, at mine. You have dished me up, like a savoury omelette, to gratify the appetite of the reading rabble for gossip.
